&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locally Employed Associate Specialist – Community Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary £56,133 to £92,401 per annum for 40 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part time posts available, flexible working options&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Current vacancies Community Hospitals Skegness and Spalding Fixed Term Winter Contracts until 31/3/2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an Associate Specialist/experienced Specialty Doctor/Registrar looking for a different way of working?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are Lincolnshire Community Health Services NHS Trust (LCHS), the primary community healthcare provider in Lincolnshire delivering community-based services aimed at supporting people to manage their own health at home and reducing the need for people to go into hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We care for thousands of patients every day, in partnership with other health and social care services, to deliver joined-up care in community settings. The intention is to provide good out of hospital care and avoid admissions into acute hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By providing community-based services aimed at preventing health problems from getting worse, we help to reduce the need for people to go into hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for proactive, dedicated and dynamic individuals who can be part of a fast- moving, innovative and ambitious team, dedicated to supporting members of our communities to manage their own health at home and reduce the need to go into hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are rated ‘Outstanding’ by the Care Quality Commission (only 4 community trusts in the country who are) and are playing an integral part in shaping future health service provision countywide alongside partner health and social care organisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our roles are multi-faceted supporting our Primary Care, Clinical Assessment Service (CAS), Community Hospitals and Urgent Treatment Centre&#39;s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Just a flavour of this role:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing a wide and reaching case load, dealing with a wide range of presenting health care needs and undiagnosed problems across our 24/7 services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide remote support to telephone consultations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrated teams within our in-patient community hospitals; step-down patients for rehab from local acute hospitals; step-up patients from the community requiring investigation and medical management of problems; end of life care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return, we can offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Local Associate Specialist Doctor Pay Scale of £56,133 to £92,401 per annum&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Study leave – 1 x session per week + mandatory training + 4 additional days to suit staff member&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding CQC rating&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Varied, interesting and challenging work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical leadership structure to provide support and mentoring&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free medical indemnity cover&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated career pathways&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health &amp; Wellbeing service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holiday pay of 32 days per annum, plus bank holidays pro rata.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not only will you have the opportunity to flourish in a successful NHS Trust, Lincolnshire offers some of the best schools in the country, affordable housing, a world class golf course in Woodhall Spa and a great standard of living in one of the many picturesque market towns, villages or a thriving city.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Low cost of living/house prices – Rightmove Lincolnshire&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent schools – Schools in Lincolnshire&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;City, Countryside, Coast – Visit Lincoln&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct rail connections by LNER, East Midlands Railway and Northern Rail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to Apply?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To view the full advert and job description which includes specific details regarding the role, or apply for any of our medical vacancies please visit our website, or apply on line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to discuss further or to arrange a visit, please contact;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Janine Elson, Deputy Medical Director at janine.elson@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Don’t know much about Lincolnshire, why not come and spend a weekend to see the sites and meet members of the team?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJanine ElsonJob titleDeputy Medical DirectorEmail addressjanine.elson@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
